# =============================================================================
# Job Pipeline — Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
#   ⚠️  SECURITY WARNING  ⚠️
#   This file is a TEMPLATE — do NOT put real secrets here.
#   Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and populate it locally.
#
#   Never commit `.env` to version control — it contains your live
#   DeepSeek API key and is explicitly listed in `.gitignore`.
#
#   If you accidentally commit `.env`, rotate your API key immediately.
#
# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED — DeepSeek API Access
# =============================================================================
#
# Your DeepSeek API authentication token. The pipeline uses this key to:
#   - Score job descriptions against your career profile (score.js)
#   - Generate tailored resumes and cover letters (generate.js)
#   - Rate document quality with the auto-assessor (generate.js)
#
# Get your key from: https://platform.deepseek.com/api-keys
# The 'deepseek-chat' model is hardcoded and is not configurable.
#
# Example:  DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-abc123def456ghi789jkl012
#
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — Pipeline Server Port
# =============================================================================
#
# The HTTP port used by:
#   - Express server (server/server.js)  — hosts dashboard + harvest endpoint
#   - Event broadcaster (eventBroadcaster.js)  — pushes SSE events to dashboard
#
# Both read the same PIPELINE_PORT env var. If unset, defaults to 3000.
#
# Use a different port if 3000 is already in use on your system:
#   PIPELINE_PORT=3001
#
# Tests automatically set PIPELINE_PORT=3001 to avoid port conflicts.
#
PIPELINE_PORT=3000

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — Pipeline Base Directory
# =============================================================================
#
# The root directory where the pipeline stores jobs/, resumes/, archive/,
# and applications.json. If unset, defaults to the project root directory.
#
# This is useful if you want to keep data outside the project tree (e.g.,
# on a separate drive or outside OneDrive sync range).
#
# Example:  PIPELINE_BASE_DIR=C:/pipeline-data
#
# PIPELINE_BASE_DIR=
